keywords:
  - large language models
  - belief contamination
  - hallucination evaluation
  - manipulation check
  - benchmark construction
  - LLM evaluation protocol
abstract: >
  BCBench is a controlled four-group experimental protocol and 40-pair benchmark
  dataset for evaluating cross-claim belief contamination in large language models:
  whether accepting a false belief about one claim alters epistemic behavior toward
  a second, structurally unrelated claim. The repository includes the frozen
  protocol specification, dataset, judge implementation and validation pipeline
  (including independent blind adjudication artifacts), full experimental results,
  and analysis code.
